CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 11, 1966, pg. 1A, reads: "NAACP PICKETS U. S. STEEL MAIN HEADQUARTERS - As the national, state and local levels of NAACP picketed U. S. Steel Corp.'s main headquarters building at Fifth Ave. and William Penn Way, Downtown, Monday... Center photo shows Pittsburgh NAACP President Byrd Brown and Penna. NAACP President Henry Smith picketing. They were joined by a half dozen NAACP presidents from Southwestern Penna. areas and by Herbert Hill, national NAACP Labor Secretary".
TitMainTitle: Protesters outside of U. S. Steel building, including Byrd Brown with sign reading "NAACP PGH Branch," and Judge Henry Smith with sign reading "US Steel still has segregated facilities in 1966," Downtown
